messages.message: If my localhost is running realllllllyyyy slowly to the point where I almost can't use it, but dogfood is fine, is that a me problem or an instabase problem?
It was a me problem, but I still don't know why :shrug: Restarted all my services and it started running the right speed again

I’ve been having an issue where sometimes the docker daemon will consume A LOT of memory (more than twice what I allocate). I’ve gotten to where I restart docker to “fix” it, but if more people run into the problem it might be worth diving deeper :slightly_smiling_face:
